          "tz": 0
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
          "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-10-30 20:28:12.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-10170 osp: fix the problem of missing wakeups",
        "message": "LU-10170 osp: fix the problem of missing wakeups\n\nosp_sync_add_rec() adds the osp_device into the committed wakeup\nlist before inserting the actual record, this could cause a problem\nthat the device may be taken out of the list by a previous sync change\nand then this device will never send SETATTR/UNLINK RPC to OSTs\nthereafter if there is no further sync changes coming in.\n\nThis problem can be fixed by adding the device into list again after\nthe record is inserted.\n\nSigned-off-by: Jinshan Xiong <jinshan.xiong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I7da955d71c0c6b0f6a708014a11d56c0e50da27b\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
